## Center Align

### Center Align Elements

To horizontally center a block element, useÂ `margin: auto;`

Setting the width of the element will prevent it from stretching out to the edges of its container.

<aside>
ðŸ’¡ **Note:**Â Center aligning has no effect if theÂ `width`Â property is not set (or set to 100%).

</aside>

### **Center Align Text**

To center only *the text inside an element*, useÂ `text-align: center;`

### **Center an Image**

To center an image, set left and right margin toÂ `auto`Â and make it into aÂ `block`Â element:

