## Left & Right Align

### Left & Right Align - Using `position`

One method for aligning elements is to useÂ `position: absolute;`

```css
/* Example using `position: absolute;` */

.right {
  position: absolute;
  right: 0px;
  width: 300px;
  border: 3px solid #73AD21;
  padding: 10px;
}
```

### Left & Right Align - Using `float`

Another method for aligning elements is to use theÂ `float`Â property:

```css
/* Example using float */

.right {
  float: right;
  width: 300px;
  border: 3px solid #73AD21;
  padding: 10px;
}
```